  "derived_from": [],
  "is_vocab": false,
  "stimulus_html": "<p>Proteins can be cleaved specifically at the amide bond on the carboxyl side of methionine residues by reaction with cyanogen bromide, BrC≡N.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBam9hIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--2f8dd7e71c41c2a38c612df212cbbd80032ba4ea/OChem_26_EC_016.jpg\" alt=\"\"></p>\n<p>The reaction occurs in several steps:</p>",
  "questions": [
    {
      "id": 349885,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The first step is a nucleophilic substitution reaction of the sulfur on the methionine side chain with BrCN to give a cyanosulfonium ion, [R<sub>2</sub>SCN]<sup>+</sup>. Show the structure of the product, and propose a mechanism for the reaction.</p>",
      "answers": [],
      "hints": [],
      "formats": [
        "free-response"
      ],
      "combo_choices": []
    },
    {
      "id": 349886,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The second step is an internal S<sub>N</sub>2 reaction, with the carbonyl oxygen of the methionine residue displacing the positively charged sulfur leaving group and forming a five-membered ring product. Show the structure of the product and the mechanism of its formation.</p>",
      "answers": [],
      "hints": [],
      "formats": [
        "free-response"
      ],
      "combo_choices": []
    },
    {
      "id": 349887,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The third step is a hydrolysis reaction to split the peptide chain. The carboxyl group of the former methionine residue is now part of a lactone (cyclic ester) ring. Show the structure of the lactone product and the mechanism of its formation.</p>",
      "answers": [],
      "hints": [],
      "formats": [
        "free-response"
      ],
      "combo_choices": []
    },
    {
      "id": 349888,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The final step is a hydrolysis of the lactone to give the product shown. Show the mechanism of the reaction.</p>",
      "answers": [],
      "hints": [],
      "formats": [
        "free-response"
      ],
      "combo_choices": []
    }
  ],
